<page number="2" position="absolute" top="0" left="0" height="1188" width="918">
	<fontspec id="7" size="13" family="Times" color="#000000"/>
<text top="55" left="90" width="103" height="13" font="1">Security Council</text>
<text top="55" left="733" width="95" height="13" font="1">4076th meeting</text>
<text top="73" left="90" width="102" height="13" font="1">Fifty-fourth year</text>
<text top="73" left="710" width="118" height="13" font="1">30 November 1999</text>
<text top="110" left="122" width="279" height="13" font="5"><i>The meeting was called to order at 6.25 p.m.</i></text>
<text top="146" left="90" width="153" height="13" font="7"><b>Adoption of the agenda</b></text>
<text top="182" left="122" width="157" height="13" font="5"><i>The agenda was adopted.</i></text>
<text top="218" left="90" width="358" height="13" font="7"><b>The situation concerning the Democratic Republic of the</b></text>
<text top="236" left="90" width="42" height="13" font="7"><b>Congo</b></text>
<text top="272" left="122" width="327" height="13" font="7"><b>Second report of the Secretary-General on the</b></text>
<text top="290" left="122" width="327" height="13" font="7"><b>United Nations Preliminary Deployment in the</b></text>
<text top="308" left="122" width="327" height="13" font="7"><b>Democratic Republic of the Congo (S/1999/1116</b></text>
<text top="326" left="122" width="77" height="13" font="7"><b>and Corr.1)</b></text>
<text top="362" left="122" width="97" height="13" font="7"><b>The President:</b></text>
<text top="361" left="225" width="223" height="13" font="1">I should like to inform the Council</text>
<text top="379" left="90" width="358" height="13" font="1">that I have received a letter from the representative of the</text>
<text top="397" left="90" width="358" height="13" font="1">Democratic Republic of the Congo in which he requests to</text>
<text top="415" left="90" width="358" height="13" font="1">be invited to participate in the discussion of the item on the</text>
<text top="433" left="90" width="358" height="13" font="1">Council's agenda. In conformity with the usual practice, I</text>
<text top="451" left="90" width="358" height="13" font="1">propose, with the consent of the Council, to invite that</text>
<text top="469" left="90" width="358" height="13" font="1">representative to participate in the discussion, without the</text>
<text top="487" left="90" width="358" height="13" font="1">right to vote, in accordance with the relevant provisions of</text>
<text top="505" left="90" width="358" height="13" font="1">the Charter and rule 37 of the Council's provisional rules of</text>
<text top="523" left="90" width="64" height="13" font="1">procedure.</text>
<text top="559" left="122" width="260" height="13" font="1">There being no objection, it is so decided.</text>
<text top="596" left="122" width="13" height="13" font="5"><i>At</i></text>
<text top="596" left="148" width="18" height="13" font="5"><i>the</i></text>
<text top="596" left="180" width="58" height="13" font="5"><i>invitation</i></text>
<text top="596" left="251" width="12" height="13" font="5"><i>of</i></text>
<text top="596" left="276" width="18" height="13" font="5"><i>the</i></text>
<text top="596" left="308" width="61" height="13" font="5"><i>President,</i></text>
<text top="596" left="383" width="22" height="13" font="5"><i>Mr.</i></text>
<text top="596" left="418" width="30" height="13" font="5"><i>Ileka</i></text>
<text top="614" left="122" width="327" height="13" font="5"><i>(Democratic Republic of the Congo) took a seat at the</i></text>
<text top="632" left="122" width="86" height="13" font="5"><i>Council table.</i></text>
<text top="668" left="122" width="91" height="13" font="7"><b>The President</b></text>
<text top="667" left="212" width="236" height="13" font="1">: The Security Council will now begin</text>
<text top="685" left="90" width="358" height="13" font="1">its consideration of the item on its agenda. The Council is</text>
<text top="703" left="90" width="358" height="13" font="1">meeting in accordance with the understanding reached in its</text>
<text top="721" left="90" width="117" height="13" font="1">prior consultations.</text>
<text top="757" left="122" width="327" height="13" font="1">Members of the Council have before them the second</text>
<text top="775" left="90" width="358" height="13" font="1">report of the Secretary-General on the United Nations</text>
<text top="793" left="90" width="358" height="13" font="1">Preliminary Deployment in the Democratic Republic of the</text>
<text top="811" left="90" width="264" height="13" font="1">Congo, document S/1999/1116 and Corr.1.</text>
<text top="847" left="122" width="327" height="13" font="1">Members of the Council also have before them</text>
<text top="865" left="90" width="358" height="13" font="1">document S/1999/1207, which contains the text of a draft</text>
<text top="883" left="90" width="358" height="13" font="1">resolution prepared in the course of the Council's prior</text>
<text top="901" left="90" width="83" height="13" font="1">consultations.</text>
<text top="937" left="122" width="327" height="13" font="1">It is my understanding that the Security Council is</text>
<text top="955" left="90" width="358" height="13" font="1">ready to proceed to the vote on the draft resolution</text>
<text top="973" left="90" width="358" height="13" font="1">(S/1998/1207) before it. If I hear no objection, I shall put</text>
<text top="991" left="90" width="222" height="13" font="1">the draft resolution to the vote now.</text>
<text top="109" left="512" width="260" height="13" font="1">There being no objection, it is so decided.</text>
<text top="146" left="512" width="222" height="13" font="5"><i>A vote was taken by show of hands.</i></text>
<text top="182" left="481" width="62" height="13" font="5"><i>In favour:</i></text>
<text top="217" left="512" width="316" height="13" font="1">Argentina, Bahrain, Brazil, Canada, China, France,</text>
<text top="235" left="512" width="316" height="13" font="1">Gabon, Gambia, Malaysia, Namibia, Netherlands,</text>
<text top="253" left="512" width="316" height="13" font="1">Russian Federation, Slovenia, United Kingdom of</text>
<text top="271" left="512" width="316" height="13" font="1">Great Britain and Northern Ireland, United States of</text>
<text top="289" left="512" width="52" height="13" font="1">America</text>
<text top="326" left="512" width="95" height="13" font="7"><b>The President:</b></text>
<text top="325" left="612" width="216" height="13" font="1">There were 15 votes in favour. The</text>
<text top="343" left="481" width="347" height="13" font="1">draft resolution has been adopted unanimously as</text>
<text top="361" left="481" width="144" height="13" font="1">resolution 1279 (1999).</text>
<text top="397" left="512" width="316" height="13" font="1">The Security Council has thus concluded the present</text>
<text top="415" left="481" width="317" height="13" font="1">stage of its consideration of the item on its agenda.</text>
<text top="452" left="481" width="318" height="13" font="7"><b>Expression of farewell by the outgoing President</b></text>
<text top="488" left="512" width="100" height="13" font="7"><b>The President:</b></text>
<text top="487" left="621" width="207" height="13" font="1">Before adjourning this meeting,</text>
<text top="505" left="481" width="347" height="13" font="1">since this is the last meeting of the Slovene presidency of</text>
<text top="523" left="481" width="347" height="13" font="1">November 1999, I would like to express on behalf of my</text>
<text top="541" left="481" width="347" height="13" font="1">delegation our gratitude to all the members of the</text>
<text top="559" left="481" width="347" height="13" font="1">Security Council. We are grateful for the assistance and</text>
<text top="577" left="481" width="347" height="13" font="1">understanding that members have rendered to the</text>
<text top="595" left="481" width="347" height="13" font="1">presidency throughout this month, for the moral support</text>
<text top="613" left="481" width="347" height="13" font="1">and for the great spirit in which the Council worked in</text>
<text top="631" left="481" width="151" height="13" font="1">the month of November.</text>
<text top="667" left="512" width="316" height="13" font="1">We are particularly grateful to Mr. Stephanides and</text>
<text top="685" left="481" width="347" height="13" font="1">Ms. Blenman and their team for the very efficient support</text>
<text top="703" left="481" width="347" height="13" font="1">and assistance which has been ever available to the</text>
<text top="721" left="481" width="347" height="13" font="1">President of the Security Council. They have helped</text>
<text top="739" left="481" width="347" height="13" font="1">greatly in overcoming a variety of technical and other</text>
<text top="757" left="481" width="228" height="13" font="1">obstacles to the work of the Council.</text>
<text top="793" left="512" width="316" height="13" font="1">I would like to express today our particular</text>
<text top="811" left="481" width="347" height="13" font="1">admiration for the interpreters, who have been with us for</text>
<text top="829" left="481" width="33" height="13" font="1">many</text>
<text top="829" left="530" width="27" height="13" font="1">long</text>
<text top="829" left="573" width="37" height="13" font="1">hours,</text>
<text top="829" left="627" width="51" height="13" font="1">showing</text>
<text top="829" left="694" width="30" height="13" font="1">great</text>
<text top="829" left="740" width="50" height="13" font="1">patience</text>
<text top="829" left="806" width="22" height="13" font="1">and</text>
<text top="847" left="481" width="347" height="13" font="1">professionalism. They have made our agreements and</text>
<text top="865" left="481" width="347" height="13" font="1">differences perfectly understood. This has helped us in</text>
<text top="883" left="481" width="60" height="13" font="1">our work.</text>
<text top="919" left="512" width="316" height="13" font="1">We are grateful to the entire staff of the Secretariat,</text>
<text top="937" left="481" width="347" height="13" font="1">all the document officers, technicians, conference room</text>
<text top="955" left="481" width="347" height="13" font="1">officers, security officers and others who make the</text>
<text top="973" left="481" width="347" height="13" font="1">operation of the Security Council possible. The Security</text>
<text top="991" left="481" width="347" height="13" font="1">Council is a complex mechanism, and without all this</text>
<text top="1009" left="481" width="307" height="13" font="1">support it would not be able to organize its work.</text>
<text top="1084" left="90" width="8" height="13" font="1">2</text>
</page>
<page number="3" position="absolute" top="0" left="0" height="1188" width="918">
<text top="55" left="90" width="103" height="13" font="1">Security Council</text>
<text top="55" left="733" width="95" height="13" font="1">4076th meeting</text>
<text top="73" left="90" width="102" height="13" font="1">Fifty-fourth year</text>
<text top="73" left="710" width="118" height="13" font="1">30 November 1999</text>
<text top="109" left="122" width="327" height="13" font="1">This has been an interesting and exciting month. I</text>
<text top="127" left="90" width="358" height="13" font="1">believe that the Council has taken several important</text>
<text top="145" left="90" width="358" height="13" font="1">decisions. I think that we can conclude this month with a</text>
<text top="163" left="90" width="180" height="13" font="1">certain degree of satisfaction.</text>
<text top="199" left="122" width="327" height="13" font="1">As the outgoing President, I would like to inform the</text>
<text top="217" left="90" width="358" height="13" font="1">Council that the reception that I am hosting is starting</text>
<text top="235" left="90" width="251" height="13" font="1">within a few minutes and all are invited.</text>
<text top="272" left="122" width="185" height="13" font="5"><i>The meeting rose at 6.30 p.m.</i></text>
<text top="1084" left="821" width="8" height="13" font="1">3</text>
</page>
